Step 1: Identify the total debt (liabilities) and total assets at the end of the period.
• From the balance sheet, the total liabilities are given as Total Current Liabilities = 3,376,304.04.
• The total assets are provided as Total Assets = 19,520,226.07.

Step 2: Compute the Debt to Asset Ratio as follows:
  Debt to Asset Ratio = (Total Liabilities) / (Total Assets)
  = 3,376,304.04 / 19,520,226.07
  ≈ 0.1729

Step 3: Rounding this value (typically to two decimal places), we get 0.17.

Thus, the final answer in the required format is:
